<HEAD>Boy Allegedly Points Shotgun at Teacher, Students</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GLENDALE, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A high school student apparently
despondent over being rejected by a girl waved a loaded shotgun at
a teacher and four other students and threatened to kill himself,
then gave up the weapon to the teacher.
   No one was hurt in the incident Thursday morning at Independence
High School, which lasted only about five minutes, said police
spokesman Marshall Downen.
   ``The band teacher actually talked him into giving up the gun.
The student unloaded the weapon and handed the empty gun to the
teacher,'' Downen said.
   The student, identified as Roy H. Rosenboom, 16, was taken to
West Valley Camelback Hospital for evaluation. Downen said he would
be referred to Maricopa County juvenile authorities for
investigation of five counts of endangerment.
   Students said Rosenboom apparently had been rejected by a girl
in his school.
   ``He wanted to kill himself in front of her or kill her with
him,'' said Wendy Petty, 16, a junior at the school.
