sets the Guinness World Book record about how a bill grew in
conference.'' _ Rep. Thomas Coleman, R-Mo., calling a bill, which
ballooned 8,700 percent into a $60 million pork barrel full of
back-home booty for powerful lawmakers before the House scuttled
it, ``the perfect model of how Congress is a pork farm.''
