<HEAD>UNDATED: SUBS fifth item to CORRECT spelling of ``Edinburgh'' in
lead.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh and president of
the World Wildlife Fund, says the tunnel being built under the
English Channel poses no environmental threat to either coast.
   The prince, on a three-day visit to France, met with President
Francois Mitterrand at the presidential Elysee Palace Thursday to
discuss environmental damage to the Loire River and other
ecological issues.
   The prince told reporters the World Wildlife Fund was concerned
about pollution in the Loire, but that the railroad tunnel posed
``no environmental problems for the French or British coasts.''
   Since its founding in 1961, the World Wildlife Fund has
contributed more than $130 million toward 5,000 projects in 130
countries aimed at protecting animals and plants threatened with
extinction.
 
