<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Fire Fluke,0121</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Firefighters Can't Respond to Blaze</HEAD>
<DATELINE>McINTYRE, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   When the call came, the McIntyre volunteer
fire company found there was no way to get its equipment on the
road.
   The burning building was owned by Valjean Wissinger, who
happened to be at the fire station repairing a leaking gasoline
tank on a fire truck.
   Because that truck blocked the main door of the fire hall, two
other trucks couldn't get out.
   It was the first time in 23 years that the volunteer fire
company could not respond to an alarm, though firefighters from
four other communities responded.
   The fire, which investigators labled suspicious, destroyed
Wissinger's building as well as a pickup parked nearby.
