<HEAD>Man Gets 10-Year Sentence For Biting Officer's Ear</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LUBBOCK, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man has been sentenced to 10 years in
prison for biting off and swallowing part of a police officer's ear.
   A jury took only 10 minutes to find Willie Jackson guilty
Thursday of aggravated assault on a peace officer and decided on
the maximum sentence.
   Officer Brian McNeill testified that on June 11 he stopped to
help another officer who had stopped Jackson on suspicion of
driving while intoxicated.
   Officers testified that Jackson became violent, and bit off part
