<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Arms Sale,120</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Pentagon OKs Sale to Thailand</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Pentagon notified Congress on Friday it
had approved a sale of self-propelled howitzers and various other
armored vehicles to Thailand.
   Assuming there are no congressional objections, the Pentagon
said Thailand would be offered 20 of the 155mm howitzers, 20
ammunition support vehicles, 11 command post carriers and 17
armored personnel carriers for about $63 million.
   ``This purchase is part of a Thai program to restructure and
modernize active army units,'' the Pentagon said. ``It will provide
increased mobility and long-range firepower.''
   The Pentagon said the U.S. Army would be responsible for
overseeing the transaction and that the prime contractors would be
Bowen McLaughlin York of York, Pa., and the FMC Corp. of San Jose,
Calif.
