<HEAD>London Stocks Narrowly Mixed In Mostly Quiet Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices were narrowly mixed Friday as
attention turned once again to speculative situations.
   ``We are fairly near the upper levels of the market,'' one
equity salesman said. ``I wouldn't expect institutions to buy at
this stage.''
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index was down 1.5
points, or 0.08 percent, at 1,829.2 at midday.
   Overall volume was moderate, with 350 million shares changing
hands by midday, compared with 212.5 million shares at the same
time Thursday.
   British inflation figures released just before midday had little
immediate impact on the market because they closely matched
expectations. However, the report confirmed inflation is still a
worry in the British economy, economists said.
   The report showed Britain's retail price index rose 0.5 percent
in September from August and was up 5.9 percent from a year
earlier. Some economists are forecasting inflation will rise to 7
percent early next year before falling back.
</TEXT>
